Figure 4 shows a schematic of the valve displacement over a period and a half of PWM operation at a very low mark–space ratio. Several time delays can be identified:


t1−t0, the time delay in opening the valve;

t2−t1, the time to open the valve once it begins moving;

t3−t2, the time delay in closing the valve;

t4−t3, the time to close the valve once it begins moving.
where t5 − t1 is the PWM period, TPWM. The minimum and maximum mark–space ratios between which a PWM-controlled valve exhibits linear behaviour are given by Topcu et al.34
